@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam defaultFontName Segoe UI
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 180
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 12
}

title DRE 3D Operating Excellence Framework
caption Reliability + Observability + Model Benchmarking + FinOps + Adoption + Governance

rectangle "Business Outcomes\nDRRI, MTTD, MTTR, Trust" as OUT #E8F4FD

rectangle "1) Reliability and SLO Control" as R1 #D5E8D4 {
  rectangle "Service SLO Catalog\n- diagnosis_latency_slo\n- deflection_success_rate\n- rule_authoring_success_rate" as R1A #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Error Budget Engine\n- burn rate\n- release gates\n- escalation" as R1B #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "2) Observability and Tracing" as R2 #DAE8FC {
  rectangle "Golden Signals\nlatency, traffic, errors, saturation" as R2A #FFFFFF
  rectangle "End-to-End Trace Spine\nrequest_id -> tool_id -> sql_id" as R2B #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Data Observability\nfreshness, schema drift, lineage breaks" as R2C #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "3) Model Performance and Benchmarking" as R3 #F8CECC {
  rectangle "Offline Benchmark Suite\ngolden prompts, golden SQL, regression checks" as R3A #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Online Evaluation\nacceptance rate, override rate, groundedness" as R3B #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Safety Metrics\nblocked_sql_rate, risky_sql_ack_rate" as R3C #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "4) FinOps and Cost Intelligence" as R4 #FFF2CC {
  rectangle "Unit Economics\ncost per suggestion, cost per saved rule" as R4A #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Cost Pattern Analytics\nby domain, model, prompt type, hour" as R4B #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Budget and Guardrails\nsoft cap, hard cap, policy fallback" as R4C #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "5) Adoption and Product Analytics" as R5 #E1D5E7 {
  rectangle "Usage Funnel\nopen -> suggest -> select -> confirm -> save" as R5A #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Trust Indicators\nacceptance, rejection reason, edit ratio" as R5B #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Domain Rollout Health\nactive domains, WAU by role" as R5C #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "6) Governance and Risk Controls" as R6 #FCE5CD {
  rectangle "Policy as Code\nSQL safety policy, approval routing" as R6A #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Audit and Evidence Pack\nwho approved, why blocked, what changed" as R6B #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Exception Lifecycle\nowner, expiry, remediation due date" as R6C #FFFFFF
}

rectangle "7) Action and Improvement Loop" as R7 #D9EAD3 {
  rectangle "Control Tower\nKPI scorecards + alerts + weekly review" as R7A #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Improvement Backlog\nprompt tuning, model routing, runbook updates" as R7B #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Release Fitness Gates\nblock release on KPI regressions" as R7C #FFFFFF
}

R1 --> R2
R2 --> R3
R3 --> R4
R4 --> R5
R5 --> R6
R6 --> R7
R7 --> OUT

R2B --> R1B : SLO burn attribution
R3B --> R4B : quality vs cost trend
R5B --> R3A : benchmark refresh
R6A --> R3C : SQL safety categories
R7A --> R1A : target recalibration

legend right
WHAT
- A measurable operating architecture for DRE 3D, not only component topology.

WHY
- Architecture quality must be proven by SLOs, model quality, cost efficiency,
  and user adoption - continuously, not as one-time design output.

HOW TO SOLVE
- Add explicit control planes for reliability, observability, model benchmarking,
  FinOps, adoption analytics, and governance.
- Tie all planes into one control tower with release fitness gates.

SOLVES
- Unclear diagnosis latency accountability
- Unknown model regression impact
- Rising cost without value signal
- Low adoption without root-cause visibility
- Weak auditability for safety decisions

MEASURED BY
- Diagnosis latency p95, deflection success rate, DRRI trend
- SQL validity and groundedness rates
- Cost per saved rule and budget variance
- Funnel conversion and weekly active users
- Policy violation rate and exception closure SLA
endlegend

@enduml
